      //fs = new FileScanner(new java.io.File("C:\\Users"));   	                                                                                    	// If successful then return a BufferedReader instantiated using provided InputStream and directs reader's buffering size towards the same value.. Provided by fs or default Charset is platform’s current charset (i.e., no specified). This must be followed with call to close() on this file scanner instance, if not done properly it might lead into inappropriate operation related security-sensitive operations A01_BrokenAccessControl
